How to run, insert and delete a cell in a notebook
- file, rename notebook, code and run (run selected or all cells)
- plus symbol to add a new cell (edit to delete cell)

Work with multiple notebooks
- click plus button on the toolbar and select the file you want to open
- alternatively click file (New launcher)
- you can place notebooks side by side


Present the notebook
- create markdown to add titles (code --> mardown)
- slides functionality allows you to deliver code, visualization, text
  and outputs of the executed codes as part of a project

Shut down the notebook session
- releases their memory
- click stop icon on the sidebar (terminate all sessional at once or 
  shut them down indivualiy)
- "no kernel" at the top right
